english: Teacher, what are we going to see at the riverside?
We are going to see dragonflies.

bnn: Sinsi, na ma'aq mita ihan ba'av ta sadoan to?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see in the mountains?
We are going to see butterflies.
What are we going to do in the fields?

bnn: Monhan ata qomah sado imita sinsoaz to lamoqo, asa mananolo i na haiza qaloa sin baqosaz.
english: We are going to see the corn we grow in the fields, but you need to be aware of the ants and bees.

bnn: Sinsi, na monhan ata vanglaz lingqaol?
english: Teacher, are we going to swim in the river?

bnn: Nii, mon ita ata sado talingkokas.
english: No, we are going to see dragonflies.

bnn: Sinsi, na monhan ata qomah masoaz sanglav?
english: Teacher, are we going to grow some vegetables in the fields?
We are going to loosen the soil today.

bnn: Laopan sak haip sadoo miqomis to talingkokas.
english: Today is the first time I see real living dragonflies.

bnn: Baii, asa ak sa talikoan, manao'az saa.
english: Yeh! Wow! I love butterflies. They are very beautiful.
Those are not butterflies. They are bees.

bnn: Idi a sado, kato mon han daqvisan to dangianan.
english: Come here and take a look. Don't go too far!

bnn: Uo, ni am mon han daqvisan to dangianan.
english: Got it, we won't go anywhere too far.

bnn: Kato tindankol, madaokdaok ka modandan diaqnaip na motinkol.
english: Don't run and walk slowly lest you fall down.
I want to see them right away.
How do you go to the block-house?
How does he go to the hospital?
How do you go to Penghu?
I go to Penghu by plane.

bnn: Ton daza ak qato monhan Poonho.
english: I go to Penghu by boat.

bnn: Ton ma'aq Abos son monhan kako?
english: How does Abus go to school?

bnn: Ton daza Abos son laihlaihsapoz monhan kako.
english: Abus goes to school by train.
How does Talum go to church?
Talum goes to church by bicycle.

bnn: Ton daza as mahaipi monhan kako?
english: Do you go to school by MRT?

bnn: Nii, ton daza ak vaso monhan kako.
english: No, I go to school by bus.
Do you go to school by bicycle?

bnn: Uo, ton taontaon ak monhan kako.
english: Yes, I go to school by bicycle.

bnn: Ton daza as haiiai to laihlaih sapoz monhan takaoo?
english: Do you go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail?

bnn: Uo, ton daza ak haiiai to laihlaih sapoz monhan takao.
english: Yes, I go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail.

bnn: Ton daza naopa as laihlaih sapoz i hikoki monhan taito?
english: Are you going to Taitung by train or by plane?

bnn: Ton daza ak hikoki, ton daza hikoki mastan haiiai i laihlaih sapoz.
english: I will take the plane because it is faster than the train.

bnn: Monhan kiokai a ton daza naopa as vaso a anak naopa ontin?
english: Are you going to drive to the church or take the bus?

bnn: Anak ak ontin monhan kiokai. Anak ontin a mastan ton daza vaso masihal.
english: I will drive to the church because it is more convenient than the bus.

bnn: Mishoan so lomaq kamadaing to babalivan?
english: Is the market close to your house?

bnn: Daqvisan nan. Ton otovai ak monhan kamadaing to babalivan.
english: No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.
Is the post office close to the school?
Yes, it is within walking distance.
Is the restaurant close to the station?

bnn: Minahan papaloan tananak hima pongkan na maqto taodadip.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.
I would like to visit you.

bnn: Uka ak haip han lomaq, kilim domah to qani'anan.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

bnn: Haiza soo laqbingin ail'oan? Mom so'oan ak tinonqo in kilim soo.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.

bnn: Azoq'naip, ihan ak lomaq mantala soo.
english: Sure, I will wait for you at home.

bnn: Maqto ak siza qalinga? Asa ak kiloko.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

bnn: Nii ak masihal sadoan. Nii amin na pa'tilasan sankonon, azoq nii.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.
Thank you for accepting the interview.
You are welcome. What would you like to know?

bnn: Asa bazbaz so'oan to maqamaq as qabas maindodoaz an?
english: What do you do when you are young?
I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

bnn: Takihan soo amin ovaz'az zon asang?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?
No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

bnn: Saipok ak tas'a aso sin tas'a loqei, inak ainkon amin tasto lomaq.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

bnn: Saipok ak amin tas'a ngaon, maqai haiza saipokon a na nii to hanimolmol.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

bnn: Asa ak mapasnava soo palioni qanop to samoh.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

bnn: Ni nak madia qansaipon, maqai naipok a taqoa topa aas.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.

bnn: Amo qanop to qaimansot haiza naopa samo?
english: Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?

bnn: I nam qanop to qaimansot ni to maqto patidoan binanao'az.
english: Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.
Then, can women go hunting together?

bnn: Nito maqto, nii amin binanao'az maqto qanop.
english: No, women cannot go hunting either.

bnn: Atol, okin lomaq davos, ipin as ma daliv davos.
english: Atul, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.

bnn: Haizan totovangan ta tas'a paan, nin ma daliv ao?
english: There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!

bnn: Mavai tas'a paan, ipin moqnang ma daliv dosa paan.
english: One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

bnn: Ma daliv ak davos, haiza moo?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?
Yes! How many bottles do you need?

bnn: Daliv ak dosa paan, na ma daliv van ak tas'a tilas.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.

bnn: I han di tilas, haizan soo na asa on?
english: Here is the rice, what else do you need?

bnn: Na ma daliv an ak niboh, haiza moo?
english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

bnn: Ma daliv ak potoq imah to holos.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.

bnn: Aivin ak tas'a madiav to holos.
english: Please give me the clothes in blue.

bnn: Talom, mon isaq as sangan? Tindangol as?
english: Talum, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

bnn: Nii, mim dangaz ak bai nak ma daliv sanglav.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

bnn: Maopata qan, haiza soo sanavan ail'oan? Na moskon naopa as zako ma'on qaising?
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?

bnn: Nii maqto, na ma daliv ak holos.
english: No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

bnn: Miqomisang, piaq di sinloqos to sanglav von soi?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

bnn: Sanglav tas'a sinloqos maposan to soi.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?
Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

bnn: Aivin ak dosa sinloqos sanglav sin tas'a tingting to hotan.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

bnn: Laong, sipongol ak madas ispapatas, maqto as pasimol zako?
english: Laung, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

bnn: Uka nak amin, isia aipi Abos.
english: I don't have one either. This is Abus's.

bnn: Dooq i maqto naopa mohiav pasimol zako? Hai'iai aak masoqai soo.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.

bnn: Uningan, mindangaz amin zako matomasqain i Abos.
english: Thank you and thank Abus for me.
I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?

bnn: Asang aak simol i tao to haqil
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

bnn: Uo, kato sipongol soqaisav i taltion in.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

bnn: Nii an as masoqis zako isqaqaisqais.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.

bnn: Mavia inak to isqaqaisqais is oka sadoan.
english: Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to Talum?

bnn: Nii ak niap, on ita ok topa i.
english: I don't know. I will go and ask her.

bnn: Tangos ak pasimol so inak to isqaqaisqais.
english: I will lend you my eraser first.

bnn: Sani, sia Vilian pasimol soo malhapavon to holos i?
english: Sani, did Vilian lend you this coat?

bnn: Nii, isia aipi inaak tina sinbaliv pai'naak
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

bnn: Lomav to malhapavon to holos masdang toza iso.
english: Lumav's coat is the same as yours.

bnn: Mataqdong istaa palhapavon to holos, nii naam maszang a patas.
english: His coat is black, so our colors are different.

bnn: Abos, simol as soi ihan Vilian ta?
english: Abus, did you borrow money from Vilian?

bnn: Haiza, na soqaisok nao haip a, sipongol ak madas soi.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.

bnn: Uo, in dangaz ok as taqo Vilian.
english: Okay, I will tell Vilian for you.

bnn: Asa ka qamotis to kosian mal'qato madamo. Asa ka tikolas to kosian mal'haqo mosqot madamo. Maopata nano isdadamo.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

bnn: Maopata qan, minlaliva in ak, panqan ni ak odamoan.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

bnn: Moqnan ak masnava so piqao matasi malqato sin malhaqo mosqot to haqo.
english: Then I will teach you how to make two traps, the stone pressure trap and the neck trap.

bnn: Azoqnaip, mastan to masihal! Na maqtoin ak qabasin odamoan taklilibos.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

bnn: Mada'vasin a qoma to ismot, ipin as monhan patilasan ta siza qaol, monhan ata qomah.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

bnn: Antan ngalan i tangaa, osadoan as i monkonbo in patilasan.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

bnn: Mananoloa siza, ka'a to milo'lo, manosqait a kaol.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

bnn: Ka'a to kandapan inak to ha'qoh!
Antan han nak haqo lokis haol ta.
english: My trap is under that tree.

bnn: Haiza nak iti sin pasaqal, maqansiap ak to isaq nak haqo.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

bnn: Iskan haqo aipi, hanon zami sisilah vanlaz malhaqo iskan.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

bnn: Uka zamian ta iskanhaqo'kalala, makosia aam islalaskan madamo ki iskaan.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

bnn: Nii'ang ak maikosia islalaskan malaskan iskan, maqto as moqnin masnava zako?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?
Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

bnn: Na isnava'ak as moqnin matas'i iskan haqoh.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

bnn: Bisokbisok kin iso islalaskan non, haizing naopa iskan tis haqo, kavai sibotbot.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

bnn: Mal'oang, masmoavin a qato vidoqvidoq saa, ihaan aak dii mabotbot i islalaskan, ipin aas monhaan daiza mindangaz zako siza i tavokol.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

bnn: Sibotbot i so iskan ponipa zakoan ti, indangazok ass sibotbot.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

bnn: Manaskal daingaz, madia haip sin damoh, lamakmozan in iskan to kalala.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.

bnn: Kava ata mosoqis paqosil kaopaka taisian.
english: Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.
Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

bnn: Asihima haip, namal'oo'in laqbing, moskon ata monata qaitmal!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!

bnn: Uo i! monhaan ata sisila vanglaz qaitmal.
english: Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

bnn: Asitao laqbingin, pismali ata laqbing minaonin!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!
What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

bnn: Islonqoan laqbingin, namoskon aak tina naak monhaan kiokai lihai.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.

bnn: Sinsi! masaqbit naak a tian, asa aak monata.
english: Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.
May I go wash my hands?
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

bnn: Sinsi! masaqbit daingaz naak a bongo, namasingav aak minaonin.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

bnn: Sinsi! Namasingav aak moqnin to asitas'a, Aopa namonhaan aak ising.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.

bnn: Masaqbit istaa tian, ihaan aipa onanata'an.
english: She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

bnn: Sinsi! Masaqbit Pima ta qaongqaong, masingav aipa haip qanian.
english: Teacher, Pima has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

bnn: Mavia ka Aqoz to oka minsoma i?
Maaq aak a Vatan tanapima, taingka mangdavan.
english: My name is Vatan Tanapima, and my mom is Mrs.Doo.
What ethnic group are you from?

bnn: Maaq aak a ito Bonon to ovavaz'az.

english: Are all your family members indigenous?

bnn: Uo, Bonon toza amin aam tastolomaq.
english: Yes, my whole family is Bunun.

bnn: Nii, Bonon naak tama, Taoloo naak tina.
english: No, my father is Bunun, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.

bnn: Maaq naak tama ka topaon to Vatan, topaon naak tina to Ali.
english: My father is Vatan, my mother is Ali.

bnn: Isoo aipa tama? piaqin istaa qamisan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: Isoo aipa tama? Piaqin istaa ka qamisan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: Nii, nii aipa inaak tama, inaam asang to madadaingaz, mavaonin istaa ka qamisan.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

bnn: Piaqin soo toqas nanaz ta ka qamisan?
Mas'an qan vao'in qamisan naak a toqas nanaza.
Madaing soo toqas nanaz ta sinpaqais soo to qamisan?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

bnn: Tas'a saba to masipaton inaak a kaidaqvasan.
Talmadiin nito pasadoo, dooq i taldaqvasin aas?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

bnn: Uo i! Taldaqvasin aak. Tasto saba'in to mation naak a kaidaqvasan.
Namonhaan aak sinsi to kozkoza'an kilim i sinsi.
english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

bnn: Ihaan aipa linqaqaolan, naminhamo aipa onisin paintataiv.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

bnn: Isaq a Iboa? napaintataiv aipa onisin linqaol.
english: Where is Ibua? She's going to compete in a running competition later.

bnn: Ihaan aipa o'anpokan ta, na'ona'ook aipa.
english: She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

bnn: Ngaosang aak mabaliv moqos, nakilimok aas onisin.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

bnn: Kilima doma bonon mindangaz soo! Nakilim aak sinsi.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

bnn: Naminhamo ka Umasa haip paintataiv i matongtong mali?
english: Is Umas competing in croquet today?
No, he's competing in high jump.

bnn: Naminhaamo aas paintataiv ihaan onzokai to qani'anan?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: Naminhamo aas paintataiv ihaan onzokai to qani'anan?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: Nama'aq mita palkada'an ihaan onzokai to qani'anan?
english: What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.

bnn: Namabaliv ata kakaonon ihaan onzokai to qani'anan?
english: Will we sell food at the sports day?

bnn: Toza aas to kapanoon, kitnganagos soo ka kaitaliskangan tidankol!
english: Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.

bnn: Uka, laopang aipa monata, nasanavanin aipa molomaq.
english: No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

bnn: Ihaan aipa dadaza ta, monhana dadaza ta kilim istaa!
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

bnn: Laong qana! Talmadia'in aak nii sadoo soo. Masihal aas?
english: It's Laung. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?

bnn: Masihal i! Monso'oan aak haip pababazbaz soo.
english: I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.

bnn: Ihaan aipa pipit'aian mahanat sanglav, naloklasak aipa.
english: He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.

bnn: Monhaan aipa patolkokan madamo ki tolkok.
english: She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

bnn: Monhaan moo akia qoma kozakoza, oka ilomaq, ihaana amo lomaq ta maltatala istaa molomaq.
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.
I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.
It's so good to see you.

bnn: Maaq a bonglai ona ispaska moo, pihanav piskakazhav konbo madainpos.
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

bnn: Talmadia'in nito patantotongo, na'anpokok amo moskon maon i qaising.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

bnn: Azoq nii, monhaan ata lomaq ta, qood ki ocia pababazbaz.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.

bnn: Uninang imoo sinkasaolvaz zakoan, namodanin aak.
english: Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

bnn: Laopang a tolkok on pinataz, dasav mapolomaq mapit'ia.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.

bnn: Dooq i maqto ata ihaan laqbing to minaonin mapasadoo?
english: Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?

bnn: Maqto ihaan kako' ta? Nalo'in ata
english: How about meeting at school? We need to shoot a video.

bnn: Azoq monhaan o'anpokan ta, namainok aak holos Bonon.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

bnn: Manao'az naam asang ti ka dandan, maaq i kapopoaqin a monzakoana tantongo!
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!

bnn: Na'asang to saohaan mintalaban maltatala soo, natalmadia'ang to!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!

bnn: Mavia aas to namodaan molomaq i?
english: May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.

bnn: Mavia nito ihaan asang-daingaz ti min'oni masnanava i?
english: Why not teach in the city?

bnn: Aopa masalpo aak inaak asang, asa masaonbaas i asang to sinkadaidaz zakoan.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

bnn: Maqansiap aas matindon, simaq maisnava soo to?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

bnn: Sia inaak bai maisnava zako, mastaan aipa to maqansiap matindon ihaan asang naam ti.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.

bnn: Mavia aas to asa mapasnava matindon holos i?
english: How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

bnn: Maaq a matindon holos ona inaam to vongka', asaok aipi mapalmamaopa.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.

bnn: Maaq aipi a inaak sinkai'oni to davos.
Totoza aas to masaihoo, talmadia aas kadavos ti?
english: You're really talented. Does it take a long time to make?

bnn: Nito talmadia, mosqa taltion. ngaoson a dolaz masasngol, a pitdazaonin, sosan i tamol haan pakiong a, a mindavosin.
english: No, it only takes about three days. After steaming the sticky rice and white rice, we mix it with yeast powder, and then it can be stored in a jar.

bnn: Mababaliv aak dapoot siin salo-boqol, inaak amin to sinsosoaz.
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

bnn: Balivok amin dosa on. Piaq soi-daing?
Moskon a dosa saba to mahimaon soi-daing.
Mazima aak holos dii kon, piaq soi-daing?
english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?

bnn: Maaq aipon a hima saba soidaing.

english: It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?

bnn: Nito maqto vanaqan, na nii aak mokalo.
english: No, if I lower it further, I'll lose money.

bnn: Azoq i! Sia naak mataqdong holos balivon.
english: Alright then, I'll take a black piece of clothing.

bnn: Mabaliv aak via ton siin ngol'a ton.
english: I want this knife and this pot.

bnn: Moskon maposan saba soi-daing, kain'anakan zako matas'i, maqto talmadia ikma'aion.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

bnn: Nataqo'ak kaviaz naak mon'itia mabaliv, Maqto'ang vanaqan to tikis?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?

bnn: Azoq i! Navanaqan zako paat saba soi-daing.
english: Alright! I'll give you a discount of 400 yuan.

bnn: Mon'itia mabaliv! haiza amin holos siin tamohong isbabaliv.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

bnn: Tas'a holos tao saba to mahimaon soi-daing, tao holos a mas'an saba soi-daing.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

bnn: Mabaliv aak tas'a holos, isizaav aak baqlo to holos.
english: I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

bnn: Uninang! Asa aak mabaliv hakhak siin tinapha titi.

What were you doing just now?
I went to meet the teacher.
What are you going to do after school?
What is she doing after school?
She is going to go dancing.

bnn: oka Aping lomah cia, Ciang saikin, mabis iso naispalinoto i? natahoan ko Aping mais minsomain.
english: Aping is not at home. I am Ciang. What can I do for you? I will let him know when he comes back.

bnn: hodaspingaz, kaimin hai Ciang mas Aping! taoav ilavan.
english: Grandma, we are Ciang and Aping, please open the door for us.
I am Ciang, I am here for Umas.
Grandma, I am here to see you.

bnn: malbontoin kaso nito tantongo, malaspo saikin maso.
english: You haven't been here for a long time. I missed you so much.

bnn: Aping minsomainik kilim so namapahainan ta.
english: Aping, I am here to play with you.
Come on in! I have been waiting for you for a long time.

bnn: tanama maos inak sinsoaz to otan tan!
english: This is the sweet potato I grow. Try it!
The sweet potato is so sweet.

bnn: tozainin! tanama maos inak sinsoaz to kakaonon tan.
english: Come here! These are the fruits I grow. You should try it.

bnn: toza to madavos a sinsoaz so kakaononan.
mal-anohoa! tanama maos inka sinsoaz to ioci acipol tan!
english: Take a seat! You should try some organic corn that I grow.
Wow! The corn tastes so sweet.

bnn: ni saikin mahto maos izok, namaonik lingko cin.
english: I can't eat oranges. I will have some apples instead.
Sure, I like it very much.

bnn: masalad saikis kakaonon tan. nakaonon so
english: Let me peel the fruit for you.
Thank you. This fruit is so juicy.
I will bring you some water.
Enjoy yourself. I cooked a lot of dishes.
Oh! It smells good and looks delicious.
Enjoy yourself. There is a lot more.
I'll make myself at home then.

bnn: ik-sopaha maon i, sopahang andi pandianan.
english: Enjoy yourself. There are plenty here.

bnn: sohaphin kinaonan ko, nin mahto kohna maon.
english: I ate a lot and couldn't eat any more.

bnn: naadason ko kamo aip to hanian kosia lodon.
english: I will take you to the mountains today.

bnn: topa cina to sopah langkitaz sia lodon cia.
english: Mom says that there are lots of mosquitoes in the mountains.

bnn: na adasos masnanava kamo aip to hanian ko sia homa.
english: I will take you to the fields.
Are we going to loosen the soil?

bnn: na kosia kata aip to hanian?
na adason katas masnanava kovahlas cia.
english: Teacher will take us to the riverside.

bnn: na ko isa kata aip to hanian?
na adason katas masnanava kosia lodon cia.
english: Teacher will take us to the mountains today.

bnn: ado na kovahlas cia kata aip to hanian?
english: Are we going to the riverside today?

bnn: ni, na adason tas masnanava cia kosia lodon.
english: No, our teacher is going to take us to the mountains.

bnn: ado na kosianta aip to hanian sia lodon cia?
english: Are we going to the mountains today?

bnn: ni, na kosian ta aip to hanian sia bangkal cia.
english: No, we are going to the fields.

bnn: masnanava, na maz sadoanta sia vahlas cia?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see at the riverside?
We are going to see dragonflies.

bnn: masnanava na maz sadoanta sia lodon cia?
english: Teacher, what are we going to see in the mountains?
We are going to see butterflies.

bnn: na mapikoa ta sia bangkal cia?
english: We are going to see butterflies.

bnn: na ko sian ta bangkal cia sados imita sinsoaz to acipol, mananoloai aiza iahloloa mas vano!
english: We are going to see the corn we grow in the fields, but you need to be aware of the ants and bees.

bnn: masnanava ado na kosianta vahlas cia songhahaol?
english: Teacher, are we going to swim in the river?
No, we are going to see dragonflies.

bnn: masnanava ado na kosianta bangkal masoaz sanglav?
english: Teacher, are we going to grow some vegetables in the fields?

bnn: na kodita aip to hanian masohaz dalah.
english: We are going to loosen the soil today.

bnn: sinadoik aip to hanian mas mamantok mihomisang to salinghanoaz.
english: Today is the first time I see real living dragonflies.

bnn: ie! mazima saikis balikoan aopa manao-oaz.
english: Yeh! Wow! I love butterflies. They are very beautiful.

bnn: ni saia balikoan saia hai vano.
english: Those are not butterflies. They are bees.

bnn: isainacin sado, kakato kodahvian cia hai!
english: Come here and take a look. Don't go too far!

bnn: ong, na ni kaimin ko dahvian.
english: Got it, we won't go anywhere too far.

bnn: kakato cisdadan modaokdaok a madadan i na ciskapat.
english: Don't run and walk slowly lest you fall down.
I want to see them right away.

bnn: na ton maz kaso kosia talohan cia?
english: How do you go to the block-house?

bnn: na ontingik haiia kosia talohan cia.
na ton maz saia kosia pa-i-ioan cia?
english: How does he go to the hospital?

bnn: na kan bantas saia kosia pa-i-ioan cia.
na ton maz kason kosia Pingho?
english: How do you go to Penghu?

bnn: na ton kosbabai saikin kosia Pingho cia.
english: I go to Penghu by plane.

bnn: na ton maz kaso kosia Pingho cia?
english: How do you go to Penghu?

bnn: na ton hato saikin kosia Pingho cia.
english: I go to Penghu by boat.

bnn: na ton maz kaso ko lomah?
naton maz a Ciang kosia pasnanavan?
english: How does Ciang go to school?

bnn: tondaza Ciang mas tonhosolan kosia pasnanavan cia.
english: Ciang goes to school by train.

bnn: maz tondazas Daho cia kosia Kiokai?
english: How does Dahu go to church?

bnn: ton tampo Daho a kosia Kiokai.
english: Dahu goes to church by bicycle.

bnn: ado ton dazas ciion kosia pasnanavan?
english: Do you go to school by MRT?

bnn: ni, ton baso saikin kosia pasnanavan.
english: No, I go to school by bus.
Do you go to school by bicycle?

bnn: ong, ton tampo saikin kosia pasnanavan.
english: Yes, I go to school by bicycle.

bnn: ton dazas aopas kaoti kosia Takao?
english: Do you go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail?

bnn: ong, ton dazik kaoti kosia Takao.
english: Yes, I go to Kaohsiung by High Speed Rail.

bnn: ado ton dazas tonhosolan? ado tonkosbabai kosia Taito?
english: Are you going to Taitung by train or by plane?

bnn: ton kosbabai saikin, ton kosbabai hai mastas tondazas tonhosolan mabiskav.
english: I will take the plane because it is faster than the train.

bnn: ado tondazas tamonos, ado kana-anak onting haiia kosia Kiokai?
english: Are you going to drive to the church or take the bus?

bnn: kana-anak saikin onting haiia kosia Kiokai, mastan haiia mas tamonos cia madaozong!
english: I will drive to the church because it is more convenient than the bus.

bnn: ado malaisko imo lomah mas babalivan cia?
english: Is the market close to your house?

bnn: maldahvi, ton otobai saikin mais kosia babalivan cia.
english: No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.

bnn: ado malaisko iobiing mas pasnanavan cia?
english: Is the post office close to the school?
Yes, it is within walking distance.

bnn: ado malaisko a kakaonan mas tonbasoan cia?
english: Is the restaurant close to the station?

bnn: maisisia tonbasoan cia monapav, modadan to ima taiktaik hai taonadipin.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.

bnn: ado aizanas zikang aip to hanian?

english: I would like to visit you.

bnn: kakang minsoma i, talpatazonangik aip to hanian.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

bnn: ado dangianas kotos islonghoan? nakosoanik minaonin tantongo.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.
Sure, I will wait for you at home.

bnn: ado mahto saikin sizas iso to sing'av? napatasanko.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.

bnn: ado mahto sizas iso to haningo?
english: Would you mind if I do the video recording?

bnn: kaka i, ninak paininokanan masial sadoan, niang amin sokoan inasik.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.

bnn: oninangi, mahtoas tantongoan ko sizas hansiap.
english: Thank you for accepting the interview.

bnn: ni to makoa, namaz so asaon istopa?
english: You are welcome. What would you like to know?
What do you do when you are young?
I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

bnn: iso ovaz hai ado isia asang amin?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?
No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

bnn: saipokangik to tasa mas aso, tasa hazam, naia hai inak to aloskonan.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

bnn: saipokik amis naong to tasa, mais aiza minihomis aloskonan hai ni to mahanimolmol.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

bnn: asa-ik mapatoho mas ishahanop to samo.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

bnn: kaoman a inak hainiiapan, haito mahtoik tahos hainiiapan-ko.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.
Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?

bnn: ito bonon toza ishahanopa haimangsot hai, masamo malospingaz cioni.
english: Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.

bnn: ado mahto malospingaz malavi kodi hanop?
english: Then, can women go hunting together?

bnn: nito mahto malavi, ni amin malospingaz mahto hanop.
english: No, women cannot go hunting either.

bnn: Ciang okin lomah cin davos, kodipa mabaliv bicio.
english: Ciang, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.

bnn: aizang ilomah cia to tastopan i, kakang iahai mabaliv!
english: There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!

bnn: kaoman mais tasa, mohnang mabaliv to dosa to pan.
english: One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

bnn: na mabalivik bicio, aiza mo isbabaliv ha?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?

bnn: aiza! napia to pan balivon so?
english: Yes! How many bottles do you need?

bnn: na mabalivik to dosa to pan mas bicio nasizang mas cilas to tasto iahlop.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.
Here is the rice, what else do you need?
I want some eggs too, do you have some?
I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

bnn: na mabalivik mapotol pakiaman to olos.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.

bnn: saivik to tasa mas masanglav to olos.
english: Please give me the clothes in blue.

bnn: Ciang saiisa kaso sangan? ado saidipas ondo?
english: Ciang, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

bnn: ni, saidipik mindangaz hodaspingaz tansos sanglav.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

bnn: maopacia hangasia, ado aizanas sanavas zikang moskon ta maos haising.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?

bnn: nito mahto i, na kodipik mabaliv olos.
english: No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

bnn: mihonisang, pia to soi a sanglavan?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

bnn: andi sanglavan tasto linohos hai maposan to soi.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?
Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

bnn: saivik sanglav to dosa to linohos mas tasto cingcing to otan.
english: Please give me two bunches of vegetables and a pound of sweet potatoes.

bnn: Ciang sipongolik madas ispapatas? ado mahtoas mapasimolko.
english: Ciang, I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

bnn: okanik amin, sain hai ito Poni cia.
english: I don't have one either. This is Puni's.

bnn: ado mahto simolonko to moiav? na maaipi saikin masohis.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.

bnn: oninang, kadangzavik tahos Poni to oninang.
english: Thank you and thank Puni for me.

bnn: na masohisik mai-dosa to ahil tan.
english: I want to return these two books.
No problem and what else do you need?

bnn: na simolangik ahil tan to mai-tao.
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

bnn: ong. sohaisav mais tal-cionin, kato sipongol hai.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

bnn: niangas maisohis mas inak to ishahaishais hai.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.

bnn: amos naoka sadoanko a ishahaishais to.
english: Then, why is my eraser missing?

bnn: ado ispasimol so mas Hosong cia hai.
english: Did you lend it to Husung?
I don't know. I will go and ask her.

bnn: tangoson koas mapasimol inak to ishahaishais tan.
english: I will lend you my eraser first.

bnn: Poni, paisimolanas Hosong cias pakaapavon to olostan aopa?
english: Puni, did Husung lend you this coat?

bnn: ni, iscina sain to sinbaliv masaivko.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

bnn: mamaszang iso pakaapavonas ito Hosong cia.
english: Husung's coat is the same as yours.

bnn: isaicia pakaapavon hai matahdong, ni inam patas mamaszang.
english: His coat is black, so our colors are different.

bnn: Poni, ado sinimolas soi sia Hosong cia?
english: Puni, did you borrow money from Husung?

bnn: aiza, ana sohaisonko hanian, kazasia sipongol saikin madas soi.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.

bnn: ongat, nakadangazon koas tahos Hosong cia.
english: Okay, I will tell Husung for you.

bnn: aloaz hai konias bato malhatob, cikolas hai konias don mal-aho mais nasiza, maopacia mamantok to hansiap.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

bnn: maopacia hangsia, kalivanko hangsia amo hangsia nik odadamoan.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

bnn: ongat, naisnavan koas mas ispalhahatob anis ispal-a-aho mai-dosa to hainiiapan.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

bnn: oningdaingazang! mais maopacia hai na odadamoaninik mas minihomis matono maon.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

bnn: madadaingin ismto sia bangkal, kodipa sia soko cia izas navo, nakosianta bangkal cia.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

bnn: isia ikin to sisila cia, mais kongadahinas soko cia hai na osadoaninas.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

bnn: mananoloa i, manoshita navo a kato cidamosan.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

bnn: kato kanliva kandapas inak to sinpal-aho cia.
mansia lokis to tanngadah cia inak aho.
english: My trap is under that tree.

bnn: atonao i painhalanko at, haiiapangik to manisa inak aho a.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

bnn: salozo sian, isdadamos iskaan sia vahlas.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

bnn: okan kaimis salozo, makooni kaimis palaskan sizas iskan.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

bnn: niang saikin maikosias palaskan sizas iskan, ado mahto maisin isnavanik.
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?

bnn: ongat! taskon ta maisin kodip malaskan.
english: Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.
I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

bnn: kasoav siapav palaskana, ado sikakanis iskan i! vovohvohin a iso palaskana.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

bnn: mal-naoang i, masmoav a hatoan to cinhadinghaiding, nasibotbotonangko palaskanan, kodipa kaso siza mas ami cia.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

bnn: pai-aopav zakoan cin iskanan, nakadangazan koas sibotbot.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

bnn: masial aip to hanian taisah i, laaminas iskaan lapaonghol a kalalaan.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.

bnn: mabiskavta kolomah i, na ispahosiltas taisan a iskanan.
english: Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.

bnn: kakaa'in to lalo, mabiskava mal'anoho sian alnonohoan.
english: Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

bnn: asi'ima a aip, islongho mais koton, taskona mapahainan!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

bnn: asitao mais kotonin, kaodiip a kata kotonin pismali!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!

bnn: namapikoa a kaso mais koton to cinmot i?
english: What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

bnn: mais kotonin hai nicio, nataskon a saikin mas cina, kaosian kiokai.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.
I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.

bnn: masnanava! madahpa a inaak cian, namoonata a saikin.
english: Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.

bnn: ado mahto a saikin kaodiip tal'ima i?
english: May I go wash my hands?
It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.

bnn: masnanava! madahpa a inaak bongo, na'islongho hanian.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

bnn: masnanava! na'isloho a saikin mais mohna'in to asitasa, nakaodiip a saikin mapa'io.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.

bnn: madahpa a isaicia cian, isian onataan a saia.
english: She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

bnn: masnanava, madahpa a itoDaho bothol, islongho aip.
english: Teacher, Dahu has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

bnn: topaon a saikin to Bokon, aiza'in laopako to mas'an hamisan.
english: My name is Bukun, and I'm 10 years old.

bnn: itomaaz to sidoh a kaso to ovaaz i?
english: What ethnic group are you from?

bnn: ado Incomin amin a isoo tastolomah i?
english: Are all your family members indigenous?

bnn: oong, Bonon amin a kaimin tastolomah.
english: Yes, my whole family is Bunun.

bnn: nii, maza inaak tama hai Bonon, maza inaak cina hai Ngaingai.
english: No, my father is Bunun, and my mother is Hakka.

bnn: isima a kaso to ovaaz i?
ado isoo a adiipa to tama i? pia'in a isaicia hamisan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: aiza'in a saia to manoomon hamisan.
ado isoo adiipa to tama i? pia'in a isaicia hamisan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: nii, maza saia hai inaam to asang to madadaingaz, mavao'onin a saia to hamisan.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

bnn: pia to hamisan a isoo tohasnanaz i?
mas'anhanvao'in to hamisan a inaak tohasnanaz.
ado mapahaisdaingaz a isaicia hamisan mas soo i?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

bnn: mapahais a kaimin to ima hamisan.
tasasaba to masipaton to micio a saikin.
malbontoin nii to mapasado, ado tallaongkavin a kaso i?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

bnn: oong, tasasaba macion to micio a saikin.
oong, macionin to kongking a saikin.
nakaosian papatasan a saikin, kilim mas masnanava.
english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.

bnn: nakaodiipa a saia mavail mas vinail.
english: He's going to throw away the trash.

bnn: isian songhahaolan a saia, aopa namapasavai a saia mais sanganin.
english: He's at the swimming pool. He's going to compete in a swimming competition later.

bnn: isa a Homhom i? namapasavai a saia cisdadaan mais sanganin.
english: Where is Humhum? She's going to compete in a running competition later.

bnn: isian o'a'ampokan a saia, kaodiipik monanao mas saicia.
english: She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

bnn: natangosang a saikin mabaliv mas pinittaonghovali, nakilimonko a kaso mais sanganin.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

bnn: kilima mas doma to bonon, aopa nakaodiipik kilim mas masnanava.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

bnn: ado namapasavai a Natoh aip mas tohtohmali i?
english: Is Natuh competing in croquet today?

bnn: nii, namapasavai a saia mas macilaoskav.
english: No, he's competing in high jump.

bnn: ado namin'amo a kaso mapasavai mais pantataip to hanian i?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: oong, namapasavai a saikin mas mapasinap.
ado namin'amo a kaso mapasavai mais pantataipin to hanian i?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: namapikoa a kata mais pantataip to hanian i?
english: What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.

bnn: ado namapabaliv a kata mas kakaonon mais pantataipin i?
english: Will we sell food at the sports day?

bnn: nii, namapabaliv a kata mas i'ipon.
oa! atalo a kaso mas saoloktasa masmoav to mamanano!
english: Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!
Yes, she's sleeping in her room.

bnn: oka, laopang a saia kaonata nasanavanin minsoma
english: No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

bnn: isian a saia dosalaoto, kaodadazaa kilim mas saicia.
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

bnn: ado aiza a bonon ilomah i?
Banitol hangsia, malbonto'in nii to mapasado mas soo, malsialsialangas aopa i?
english: It's Banitul. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?
I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.

bnn: isian pipit'ia'an a saia makaling mas pandian, kaodiipik malala mas saicia.
english: He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.

bnn: kaosian pattolkokan a saia madamo mas tolkok
english: She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

bnn: oka ilomah a imoo hodasnanaz, isian homa a saia, ilomaha a kamo maltatala mas saicia
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.

bnn: malbonto'in nii to mapasado, tallaoskavin a kaso
english: I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.
It's so good to see you.

bnn: maza sain hai paimoo to bonglai, posianav piskakazavan
english: Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

bnn: malbonto'in nii to minsoma, taodanivonko amin to moskona maon mas haising
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

bnn: maso, nakaaz a saikin hood mas savil, kaosianta bokzavan mahalinga
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.

bnn: oninang mas isoo to sinpolaong namosohisin a saikin
english: Thank you for your hospitality. I have to go now.

bnn: laopang a andiip tolkokan patazon, adasavso ikdaokdaok

bnn: na'asa to maltatala saosian namintalabal. alasanin aopa i!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!

bnn: mavia to nii to isian hici masnava i?

bnn: aopa mililiskinik mas inaak to asang, hadang amin mahto masaombaas mas asang

bnn: mahansiapas macindon, to? sima a maisnavaso i?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

bnn: inaak to hodaspingaz, maza saia hai isian inaam to asang mastaan mahansiap macindon to bonon

bnn: mavia a kaso to na'asa mapasnava mas macindon i?

bnn: maza macindonan hai inaam to sin'inhomis, asa'ik mapal'aiza mas sin'inhomisatan

bnn: nii, na'aiza to tasto'islonghoan, tangoson a dolaz siin paaz ma'aliv, aat ibolan mas tamol mahaivhaiv, ongat mahtoin pongadahon sian amono

english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

podinonon hai dosasaba to maimaon to soi.

bnn: mahlisdaingaz, ado mahto vanahon to kaoman i?

bnn: nii to mahto, naminhanglasik mais vanahon.

bnn: oong iahai! siza'ik mas matahdong to olostan.

bnn: podinonon hai mapos'ansaba to soi, kai'anak'anakonko a sain ka'oni, mahto malbonto iskosia.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

bnn: mais mapishaiapik mas kaviaz to kaosianacin mabaliv hai ado mahto iasoi to kaoman i?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?

bnn: mahto! nakadazon siza to pininmas'an to vao.
english: Alright! I'll give you a 20% discount.

bnn: sadoa! aiza amin a olos siin tamoong isbabaliv.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

bnn: mais tasa olos hai taosaba to maimaon to soi. aat tao hai mas'ansaba.
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

bnn: mabalivik iahai to tasa, isizaavik mas bahlo.

bnn: mihomisang, namabalivik mas tangosol siin ininmahavan to cici.

bnn: ispako'aminin a haising, aizaanangik mas boholtana, ado namabalivas i?

bnn: oong iahai! saivavik to tasa, namabalivik haising mais mohna'in.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

bnn: oong, kankanonko sian iahloop, maimaon to soi iskaopacia.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

bnn: amo ka taic'an na kitnga' ata.
amon ka taisic'an mahaip pa' na masnava' a sinsi' i pailcicia ki kakaonon to qalinga.

Do you understand what the teacher says?

bnn: sinsi', ni' cak itqal. maqto' aso moqnang topa?
english: I don't understand. Can you repeat it again?

bnn: ni cak tan'a, pidaining ka qalinga.
english: I can't hear you, can you speak louder?

bnn: sado'a di, sisili zako moc'an masipol.

english: I forgot to bring my eraser.

bnn: dian simol isqaqaisqais ha'an qaviaz so'.

bnn: pan'iti' ata haip, na moqnang niciovi' pasado.

english: I am the son of Atul, and my name is Kavida'.

bnn: icia cak Umin panto', Sai nak ka ngan.
english: I am a student in Umin, my name is Sai.

bnn: tokao'on cia tama so a ngan?
topa'on nak ka tama to Atol.
masitoqas nak aipa', topa'on to Kavida'.
english: He is my brother, his name is Kavida'.

bnn: topa'on ciata' a ngan to Kavida'.

kaviaz nak naipa', topa'on to Sani.
english: She is my friend and her name is Sani.

mahima'on cia tama nak ka qamisan.

bnn: dosa' nak ka masitoqas cin tatini ka masinaoba'.
english: I have two brothers and sisters and one younger brother and sister.

There are four of us in our family.

Does your sister have a job?
Yes, but she is a Amis.
Yes, we are all very tall.
Does your sister go to school?

Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
I have three brothers and sisters.

Yes, I live with my mom and dad.
Do you live with your grandparents?
No, I didn't live with them.

bnn: moskon cak tamatina nak cin masitoqas nak.
english: I live with my father, mother and brother.

bnn: todip pi pal'o'onin na mocoqis monacang.

english: It's neither cold nor hot today, very comfortable.

bnn: oka' haip lohom, minsoma'in na bintoqan.

What's the weather like where you are?
We're going to have a big storm here.
Very well, out of the big sun.
I have to go to school.

bnn: makazhav va diqanin, pidai'on na holoc mainok.
english: The weather is very cold, so wear more clothes.

bnn: sodaq qai onisin na, ka'a to panpongolan na talolong.

bnn: bitvaqan sangan na' qodanan qai onisin na.

bnn: maopat qenodanan sangan pang, lovoc ca dan ni'.
english: It seems to have rained and the road is wet.

bnn: qodanan pang? toc aso lovoc ci'.

bnn: qodanan na nata' a, ni cak madas si talolong.

bnn: madaing nga lovlov va', macaqbit nak ka bongo.

bnn: madaing nga vali ka', qailipacav nak ka bongo.

I forgot to bring my chopsticks.

bnn: oka' amin nak, ina' mabaliv ata.

bnn: ina' dan ata baliv vi ispapatas o?

bnn: o, na mabalivanq cak ki isqaqaisqais.
english: Well, I still have to buy erasers.

I forgot to bring my lunchbox.

bnn: ma'on cak ito kako' to paitotongqovali'.
english: I want a nutritious school lunch.
What are you having for lunch?

bnn: madas cak ki timoqos haip, ma'aqi tongqovali' ka' moskon ata ma'on.

Let's go play basketball, shall we?
Please help me with the broom.
Okay, here's a broomstick for you.

bnn: kadangazin cak siza' i iokin, o?
english: Can you help me with the cloth?

bnn: ma'asikang cak, topa'i ka Atol to kadangazin aso siza'.
english: I'm sweeping the floor and you asked Atul to carry it for you.
The floor is dirty, go clean it.
Okay, I'll go get the cloth.
That window is very dirty, go clean it.

bnn: mal'o'ang, ni'ang cak kanaqtong ma'asik iti.
english: Wait a minute, I'm not done sweeping here yet.
I'm going to see my teacher.

bnn: malkama'aq qa aso maca pal'o'on onisin?

bnn: na moskon cak kaviaz nak tosaoc.
english: I'm going to sing with my friends.

bnn: malkama'aq qa naip maca pal'o'onin onisin?

bnn: oka' naip lomaq, haiza' so singkokoza'?

bnn: qodas, zako Sai, tao'i ka hilav vi.

bnn: Kavida', Atol cak, kilim cak so'o paqaqainan.

Please sit down and have some tea.

tonganin na tina pi'ia paitosanavan, maonin!

Okay, I'll go wash my hands.

bnn: ka'a to maz'av, bonon qa ata to'.

I ate a lot, I'm full.

bnn: na ngaosin cak modan, na moqnang cak moniti' sado so'o.

bnn: maqmotin ni, na danin cak molomaq.

Grandpa, we've come to see you.

bnn: ai maqanciap amo malasBonon! ai mailmanano'!
ina dason ko amo monha'an qoma malkamadoq.

bnn: amin sopa di pidailaz, aon na iskokoza to qaimangsot panpongolan madas.

bnn: o, sinsi', aminonin zami madas sa qaimangsot.

bnn: so'oa ka siza' i paqpaq qa.

bnn: ina', monha'an ata haip loloman ni tosmomot to loloman.

Awesome! How are we going to get there?

bnn: dian tidailaz, na mabaliv ata kipo'.

bnn: ni to makoa, ipin aso sado laoqi'.
english: It doesn't matter, then you go and watch the birds.

bnn: maqi tasbanin tas'a zikang, asa to mocoqis moniti mo'ampok.

bnn: sado cak madia ivot, haizang madia to loqi'.

bnn: makombo' ita a danom, malao ata iti lingqaol ina.

She went to the grocery store on a motorcycle.

I want to take a boat to Lanyu.
How did he get to Orchid Island?
He took a plane to Orchid Island.
What bus did he take to Kaohsiung?
He took the THSR to Kaohsiung.
Did he take a train to Taitung?
Yes, he took a train to Taitung.
Did he take a train to Taitung?

bnn: ni, tonha'an naip hikoki monha'an Taito'.

bnn: haiza', sopa tatangaoston na sado aso todaza'an baso qai.

bnn: oka' iti todaza'an ce'ion, asa aso to tonha'an kitingcia.

bnn: maqi tonha'an baso' a' talpiaq qa kaha'an kako'.
english: How long does it take to get to the school by bus?

bnn: mac'an qan hima' honcong kaha'an kako'.
maqi tonha'an kaote talpiaq qa zikang kaha'an Taicio?

bnn: na haiza' to tastozikang kaha'an Taicio.
english: I will come to Taichung in an hour.

bnn: maqi ma'onting lehleh monha'an Ulai a' talmadia?

bnn: maqi tonha'an aso ce'ion sopa lomaq nak ka'? piaq qa zikang.

bnn: ni, opa ni nak madia a qancaipan.

bnn: lomaq aso maca tinaongqovali' haip? asa cak tantongo so'oan maqto?

bnn: o na malao, na ha'an cak lomaq matala' so'o.

bnn: haza so al'o'an laqbing? asa cak macingav pailcicia ito Bonon to takiqabasan.

bnn: oka' cak laqbing, na monba'av cak.

bnn: tan'a cak to so'o dao ka malmanano maqanciap ito Bonon to iniqomican. asa cak pascingav so'o.

bnn: ni amin nak madia a qancaipon, na langatlangat antalam so'o ina.

bnn: maqto cak siza' i qaningo? na ni to panpongolan.

bnn: masiva'on qan vao'in nak qa qamisan.

I can speak Bunun and Atayal.

bnn: manaskal maqto aso latoza' pacingavan, macingav so'o paicicia qanop to samo?
english: It's a pleasure to interview you today, can you talk about the taboo of hunting?

bnn: na malao, qanglac cak monba'av qanop to vakai'ang qabas.

bnn: miqomicang, mailmanano' so haip pa sintaqo'.

bnn: mamantok nak ka sinbazbaz, ito madadaingaz to sintataqo.

bnn: maqto'in pan'iti haip pa ispabazbaz, toza' to miqomicang sala so'o.

bnn: ni to makoa, na moqnang patataqo maca lakoin dao.
na mongaosin cak modan, na lakoin ata moqnang tan'a so'o tataqo.

bnn: haizang tao linaoqoc kitda'an, aminih paiso!

bnn: piaq qa coi tas'a qalop tilac ci?

haizang masiva'on qan hima' coi di.

bnn: moavin na di maqlic, maqto hothotonang?

I want this packet of cookies.

bnn: mati'on na pingkan di, haizang so doma' siza'on?

Can I borrow money from you?

bnn: na malao! pai'on qa so simol la coi?
english: Yes! How much do you need?

bnn: minpongol cak madas si coi, maqto' aso pasimol zako ki coi?
english: I forgot to bring money, can I borrow money from you?
I don't have any money either!

bnn: ni, opa ni'ang aso macaoqis tangosang to sinimolan na.

Can I borrow your bicycle, please?

bnn: o na malao, asa to coqaison laqbing.

bnn: qodananin ni', minpongol cak madas talolong, pasimolin cak talolong so?

bnn: moaz nak tas'a ka talolong, moskon ata talolongan ina!

bnn: maqa hong di ka', sinpasimol so zako tangosang nga', coqaison ko so'oan.

bnn: maqi haizang asa'on so sado ka', taqo'in cak.
english: You can tell me what else you want to read.

bnn: na laqoaq cak macoqis si coi so i'?

bnn: ni to makoa, todip pi haizin so coi ka' na.

I'll return it to you tomorrow.
When are you going to return my book?
Didn't I return it to you yesterday?

bnn: o, ha'an cak ci'an ta simol, haip.

bnn: padangi cam mi ami' madamo ki iskan.

bnn: Maca moqnin na masnava cak soto makoqa' matas'i salozo'.

bnn: Bicokbicokin so a paniza', doqe hezin na iskan kalat! kavavain sibotbot paniza' so.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

bnn: Mal'oang, mastan na qato' vindoqvindoq. I'id cak sibotbot ti paniza', sepa caso deza kadangaz zako siza' i ami'.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

bnn: Silolo' i so a iskan sepa zako'an di. Na kadangazko aso sibotbot.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

bnn: Totoza macihal! Mastan'in haip pa sinlaskan, makmozin na kalala'.
english: Great! It is a bumper crop today with full fish baskets.

bnn: Ina kava cata mocoqes paqosli cikopa to tec'an.
english: Let's go back immediately and share it with everyone.

bnn: ni'in to moqnang kavivila, kavain molongko ha'an olongqoan ta.
english: Stop playing and quickly sit in your seat.

bnn: malihima haip, pal'o'on laqming, moskona monata kavila!
english: It's Friday today, we have a day off tomorrow. Let's go out and play together!
Great! Let's go to the riverside.
What day will it be tomorrow?

bnn: malition laqbing, matlaqming minaon tongqovalika monnata ata kavila mali!
english: Tomorrow will be Wednesday. Let's go play ball tomorrow afternoon!
What will you be doing tomorrow morning?

bnn: islongqoan laqbing, moskon cak tina monha'an kioka.
english: Tomorrow will be Sunday, I will be going to church with my mom.

bnn: asa cak motaq, monhan cak onata'an.
english: I feel like vomiting. I need to go to the restroom.

bnn: masnanava, macakbitat tian nak, asa monha'an onata'an.
english: Teacher, I have a stomachache. I need to go to the restroom.

bnn: masnanava, macakbitsala bong nak, maca tinonqovali ka na macingav to mal'o.
english: It's almost time for class to end. Wait a little longer.
Okay, take care and go home.

bnn: masnanava, na macingav cak mal'o ki moqnin malic'an, namon ising cak.
english: Teacher, I need to take a sick leave next Monday. I have to see a doctor.

bnn: cakbit tian cia, han naip onata'an ta.
english: She has a stomachache. She's in the restroom.

bnn: masnanava, cakbit cia Usong nga modan, mal'o naip haip.
english: Teacher, Usung has a sore throat. She took a sick leave today.

bnn: macak ka lizo, mac'anin nak qamisan.
english: My name is lizu, and I'm 10 years old.
What ethnic group are you from?
Are all your family members indigenous?
Yes, my whole family is Bunun.

bnn: ni,manak tama ka bonon, maq qa tina ka pot.
english: No, my father is Bunun, and my mother is Han Taiwanese.

bnn: tama so naipa? Pin qamisan cia?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: tama so naipa? pincia ka kamisan?
english: Is that your father? How old is he?

bnn: ni, manaipon na inam ha'an acangti madadaingaz. mavao'onin cia qamisan.
english: No, he is an elder of our tribe. He is 80 years old.

bnn: mastan na toqas so madia a qamisan?
english: Is your brother much older than you?

bnn: haiza to hima' qamisan na qais.
macak ka tas'asaba masipaton na tatnol.
talmadin nit pasado, dotaldaqvas sin aso?
english: I haven't seen you in a while. Have you grown taller?

bnn: o', haizin cak to tas'asabah to mation tatdol.
o, mationin nak ka tingting laopadao.
monha'an cak dangan kozkoza'an ta kilim masnanava.
english: I'm going to the office to see the teacher.
He's going to throw away the trash.

bnn: iha'an naip taldanavanta, manaip onicin na paintatav taldanav.

bnn: icaq qa Langoi? na paintataiv naip onicin tindangkol.
english: Where is Langui? She's going to compete in a running competition later.

bnn: ha'an naip o'anpokan ta, ona'ok naip.
english: She's in the auditorium. I'll go call her.
Let's go to the playground together.

bnn: ngaosang cak modan mabaliv paito tongqovali to kaonon, na kilimok aso onicin.
english: I'll go buy lunch first, and then I'll meet you later.
Let's carry the lunch boxes together!

bnn: kilima aso doma bonon, na kilim cak masnanava.
english: You find someone else, I'm going to find the teacher.

bnn: Ulang maqhaip pa paintataiv vi malodaq mali?

bnn: ni, minhamo aipon ni Sandaoncik to pantataiv.
english: No, he's competing in high jump.

bnn: dona minhamo aso paintataiv vi onzokain?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: o, minhamo cak ki tindakol to sinpaintataiv.
dona minhamo aso ki onzokai'in paintataiv?
english: Will you compete in the sports day?

bnn: na minhamo cak ki malodaq mali to sinpaintataiv.

english: What will we do in the sports day?
We will compete in tug of war.

Congratulations on getting first place! You're amazing!

bnn: oka, laopang naip modan monata, na sanavanin molomaq
english: No, she's not. She just went out and will be back in the evening.

bnn: ha'an naip dazata, mondaza'a aso kilin cia.
english: He's upstairs. You can go up and find him.

bnn: oo, lingkav, talmadin nito pasado so'o, macihal naopa aso?
english: It's lingkav. I haven't seen you in a while! How have you been?
I'm doing great! I came to chat with you.

bnn: iha'an naip pit'a'ai'an makaling sanglav, topaoko naip.
english: He's in the kitchen cooking. Let me go call him.
She went to the chicken coop to catch chickens.

bnn: oka a qodasnanaz mo ilomaq, iha'an naip qoma, hana amo lomaq maltala cia mocoqais.
english: Your grandfather is not at home. He's in the field. Wait for him to come back.
I haven't seen you in a while. You've grown taller.

bnn: sado so'o minsoma tozato manaskal la isang.

Here's a pineapple for you. Put it in the refrigerator.

bnn: talmadin nitomon'iti, loklacan zako moskon mon'iti ma'on qaising.
english: It's been a while. Let's have a meal together.

bnn: nitopin kozakoza, moaz cak qo ocia, iha'an ata boqzavan pababazbaz.
english: No need to bother. I'll just have tea. Let's sit in the living room and chat.

bnn: miqomicang ngi sinkadaidz so, na modanin cak.

bnn: laopang nga tolkokdi sinpataz, dasi molomaq daoqdaoqkon ma'on.
english: This chicken was just freshly killed. Take it home and enjoy it slowly.

bnn: moskon cak so'o laqbing patomanto ki tidonqovalin maqto?
english: Can I make an appointment with you tomorrow afternoon?

bnn: maqto, na icaq ata pataqo ki dangan pasado?
maqto ata pataqo to na iha'an sisipolanta? siza'an ata qaningo.

bnn: namonha'an o'anpopokanta, napainokan cak holocbonon mon ita.
english: Then let's go to the community center. I'll wear folk costume.

bnn: manao'az nam a poaq banoaz ha'an acing. Maca nakapoaqin na kiliming cak!
english: The cherry blossoms in our tribe are beautiful when they bloom. Come find me when the flowers bloom!

bnn: na asat taonahanin minqamisan, na macoavin halacan!
english: That would have to wait until spring. It's too late, isn't it?
Then come during our Ear Festival!
Alright! I'm looking forward to it!

bnn: macingav so'o to makoacona mocoqas ha'an acing ti miqomic?
english: May I ask why you decided to move back to the tribe?
I want to return to teach at the local school.

bnn: koacona nito iha'an bokzav masnava i paitasan?
english: Why not teach in the city?

bnn: maopa macalpo cak ki acang nak, asang macoqesang picihal li acang.
english: Because I miss my hometown and I also want to give back to the tribe.

bnn: maqanciap aso matinon, cimaq qa taqo so'o?
english: You're very skilled at weaving, who taught you?

bnn: cia qodasnao'az nak, ciata a mastan maqanciap matinon ha'an acangti to bonon.
english: It was my grandmother, she is the most skilled weaver in our tribe.

bnn: qoa caso to milickin to na asat painanam mi mation?
english: How did you develop an interest in learning weaving?

bnn: maca matin'on dika imitato sin'iqomican, na asaok naipi mangono ki maikikingna.
english: Weaving is a part of our culture, and I want to ensure its continuity.

bnn: ni, maqto tas'a islongqo'an. Ngaoson poskon ni tilacpaz ma'aliv pit'ia, na oskononin tangtangtamol mahibolhibol piszang, namaqtoin oladingon ha'an qatomoaz.
english: No, it only takes about a week. After steaming the sticky rice and white rice, we mix it with yeast powder, and then it can be stored in a jar.

bnn: haiza nak ha'an di ka dapot cin tilkom, amin anak sincoaz nak!
english: I have chili and lokiy, both grown by myself!

bnn: asaok ka holoc di, pi'iaq coi?
english: I like this piece of clothing. How much is it?
It's too expensive. Can't you lower the price a bit?

bnn: nitomakto, moqna sitikicon na song cak.

bnn: oo! nasiza azak mataqdong to holoc.

I want this knife and this pot.

bnn: moskon dosasinging coi, ain'ana'kan nak matas'i, nano to maqto talmadia okma'aion.
english: It's a total of 2000 dollars. I handmade these, and they are guaranteed to last a long time.

bnn: nataqo'an zako ka kavi'az nak to monhanati mabaliv, maqto iasoi to tikic?
english: I'll introduce my friend to buy. Can you give a further discount?
Alright! I'll give you a 20% discount.

bnn: hanoin sado! Haiza amin na holoc cin tamohong isbabaliv.
english: Come and take a look! We sell clothes and hats.

bnn: taosaba to mahima'on coi ka tas'a holoc, maca tao ka tas'asinging coi
english: One piece of clothing is 350 dollars, three pieces for 1000 dollars.

bnn: moaz cak baliv to tas'a, aivng cak ki baqlo.
english: I'll just buy one piece, please give me a new one.

bnn: miqomicang, asacak mabaliv vi qesingdolaz cin pinizaipoq titi hibolan maqav.
english: Hello, I would like to buy sticky rice and braised pork with maqaw pepper.

bnn: aminonin na qaising isbaliv. Haizang nak tinpolatana, mabaliv aso?
english: The rice is sold out. I have tana pancakes, would you like to buy them?

bnn: o! aving cak tas'aon, maca moqnin na moqnang cak baliv qaising.
english: Alright, please give me one. I'll come back next time to buy rice.

bnn: o, kangazak ko aso malading ha'an kapa, kaopata'a mahima'on coi.
english: Okay, I'll pack it in a bag for you. That'll be 50 dollars.

bnn: Maqanciap aso tan'a ki sinbazbaz is tataqo?

bnn: Nii caak maqanciap ti tokoa aso. Maqto maoqnang bazbaz.

bnn: Nii azak tan'a. Maqto tatqaiton tokoc ca qalinga?

bnn: Maoqna'ang bazbaz. Tatqaiti tokoc ca qalinga.
english: Read it again. Please speak louder.

bnn: Tataqo', minpongol azak madas is ispapatas.

bnn: Tataqo', minpongol azak madas is isqaqaisqais.

bnn: Simola ha'an taszangan soo ki isqaqaisqais.

bnn: Panca'aninti ca pisqancaipan hiip, pasadoo ca maoqnin.

bnn: Uva'az azak is Balan, topa'on ca ngaan naak to Abis.
english: I am the son of Balan, and my name is Abis.

bnn: Masisipol azak it Tiang, topaon to Bato'.
english: I am a student in Tiang, my name is Batu'.

bnn: Tokao'on ca ngaan is Tama soo?
Balan ca ngaan is Tama naak.
Toqasnanaz naak ca konan, topaon to Takoc.
english: He's my brother, his name is Takuc.

bnn: Uo, Abis ca ngaan i cia.
Nii, takoc ca ngaan i cia.
Kaot ca konan. Patinaon zako ca konan.

english: She's a friend of mine, her name is Ival.

Piin ca qamisan i cia haip.
Macan qan dosa' ca qamisan i cia haip.

Does your sister have a job?

english: Yes, we are all very tall.

Yes, they speak the ethnic language.
How many brothers and sisters do you have?

bnn: Maloskon azak tama,tina ciin toqasnanaz naak miqomic.

bnn: Laopang dangza, mintasalin ca vali ciin qaivalval.

We're going to have a big storm here.

bnn: Macial ca diqanin haan so'oan aiza?

I have to go to school.

bnn: Makazhav ca diqanin, pimadai'i ca holoc i mainok.
english: The weather is very cold, so wear more clothes.

bnn: Naso'zaq ca onin,ka'a to minpongol madas is talolong.

bnn: Qalna qodanan i bitvaqanin a sangan.

bnn: Maopa' is qainodanan a sangan pang, lovoc ca daan i.

bnn: Qodananin ca nata', nii azak madas is talolong.

bnn: Macakbit ca bongo i masqa ca hivhiv.

bnn: Qalipacav ca bongo i masqa ca vali.

bnn: Namaipata ata mabaliv is ispapatas qa?

bnn: Bazin nii, mina'onin azak haan lomaq.

I forgot to bring my lunchbox.

bnn: Moskon ata ma'on is moqos naak ca!
english: Then let's eat my lunch box together!

bnn: Ma'az ca kaonon so'o ca totosvali?

bnn: Naha'an azak sipolan ma'on is paitoqanian.
english: I want a nutritious school lunch.

bnn: Timoqos azak haip, moskon ata ma'on ca totosvali!
english: I've brought a lunchbox today, let's eat together at noon!

Okay, here's a broomstick for you.

english: Can you help me with the cloth?

bnn: Ma'asikang azak,topa'i ca Balan to kadangazi aso siza'.

bnn: Mataqdong sala ca daiseq, qaisqaisi tokoc.

bnn: Mataqdong sala ca taongkol aiza, qaisqaisi tokoc.

bnn: Namoskon azak kaviaz i naak tosasaoc.
english: I'm going to sing with my friends.

She's at home, please come in.
May I ask if Kaut is home?

bnn: Uka' a cia, Ma'az ca iskilim so'o?
english: She's not here, what can I do for you?

bnn: Qodasnanaz, Ival azak, tao'ivang ca hilav.

bnn: Tiang, Bazai azak, kilim caak so'on paqainan.

bnn: Uo na, minasaz azak so'on. Maipa'a dii qan pababazbaz!
english: Yeah! I miss you so much. Come on, let's chat!
Please sit down and have some tea.

bnn: Ua! Macial sala qodan ca savil i moo.
Uo na, macial sala sado'an ca kokotdaqon mangki.
Macacakin ca pinitdia tina paitosanavan, mahaiva qan maipadi ma'on.

Okay, I'll go wash my hands.

bnn: Mamaona, cimaqa cona nito qalmang to bonon.
english: Try to eat and drink as much as possible, you're not an outsider.

bnn: Mantanin madia ca kaonon zako, aboqanin.
english: I ate a lot, I'm full.

bnn: Namatinghilovin azak, moqnang ickoinin maipati sado so'on.

bnn: Uo, tantongoa lomaq naak ca maiza inolo'an.

bnn: Miqomicang, nadason ata haip tataqo' monca'an acang macingav is madadaingaz.

bnn: Uo, namalasbonon azam moskon madadaingaz pababazbaz.

bnn: Paqas! maqanciap qana amo malabononi! mantan macial.

bnn: Mo'amina maipadi masandailaz, ka'a to minpongol madas is naiskokoza.

bnn: Uo, tataqo', mala'aminin ca naiskokoza zami.

Not yet, it's still far away.
You go get the bird catcher.

bnn: Uo, namaipata azak posmai kis loqai'.
english: Okay, I'll go and catch the birds.

bnn: Miqomicang, namonca'an ata haip saipokan is tosmomot tantongo.

Awesome! How are we going to get there?

bnn: Mo'amina macial masandailaz, namabaliv ata kipo'.
english: Everyone line up, we are ready to buy tickets.

bnn: Maca tantangaos a loqai', maca antanhiko' a ivot, anaka amo sadoo.
english: There are birds in the front and snakes in the back.

bnn: Nito Makoa, nipin aso sado loqai' ca.
english: It doesn't matter, then you go and watch the birds.

bnn: Maca moqnin ta'a tatnolan a mocoqais ata maipati mo'inon.
english: We'll be back in an hour.

bnn: Madia sala ca loqai' ciin ivot sado'an zako.
english: I saw a lot of snakes and a lot of birds.
Hurry up, we have to go.

bnn: Moloang tokoc, mamoqo' ca mantac i naak.

bnn: Madia sala ca bonon haanti tonhapavi.
english: There are a lot of people swimming here.

bnn: Kombo' sala ca danom ha'an aiza, maqto'in ca ha'anti ata tonhapav.
english: The water is deep there, so we just swim here.

bnn: Ma'ongting ca tama naak laihlih mama' zakon maipata.

english: How does he usually go to school?

bnn: Makoa ca qodasnao'az soo maipata mabaliv is sanglav.

bnn: Tonlaihlihpokpok a cia maipata mabaliv is sanglav.

bnn: Tondaza' a cia kosbabai maipa langi.

bnn: Ma'az to laihlih tondaza'an a cia maipa takao?

Did he take a train to Taitung?
Yes, he took a train to Taitung.
Did he take a train to Taitung?

bnn: Nii, tondaza' a cia kosbabai maipa taito'.
english: No, he took a plane to Taitung.

bnn: Maiza ca olo'anlaihlih haan machoan is mangki?
english: Is there a bus stop near here?

bnn: Maiza, maipa'a tantangaos aiza na sadoo aso olo'anlaihlih.
english: Yes, if you go straight ahead, you will see the bus stop.

bnn: Ica ca mantan machoan a olo'an laihlihtingki'?
english: Where is the nearest MRT station?

bnn: Uka ha'anti olo'an laihlihtingki', mo'az aso maqto tonlaihlihkolapha.
english: There is no MRT station here, you can only take a taxi.

bnn: Machoan i lomaq moo ca babalivan?
english: Is the market close to your house?

bnn: Nii to machoan, tonlaihlihpokpok azak moncan i babalivan.
english: No, it is not, so I always ride the motorcycle to the market.
Is the post office close to the school?

bnn: Machoan hala, sohanin ta ca tananak.
english: Yes, it is within walking distance.
Is the restaurant close to the station?

bnn: maca mintasalin han i ol'oanlaihlai ha, Moqnang hima kinolotan sin'odanan na soha'annin ta.
english: It only takes five minutes after you walk out of the station.
I would like to visit you.

bnn: Uka caak ilomaq haip, ickoin a.
english: I am out today. How about another day?

bnn: Maiza inolo'an soo ca laqbing? nakilimon zako aso ca qanianin.
english: Then, are you available tomorrow? I'll visit you tomorrow afternoon.

bnn: Macial na, ilomaq caak mantala so'on.
english: Sure, I will wait for you at home.

bnn: Maqto caak sizaqalinga? nata'ion zako minpaitasan.
english: Would you mind if I do the voice recording? I would like to keep a record.
Would you mind if I do the video recording?

bnn: Qamang caak didikla sado'an, amin to ni'ang qaisvazon ca patilacan, bazin ni'ang.
english: No, I am plain and the warehouse hasn't been tidied up yet.
Then I will just take photos.
Thank you for accepting the interview.

bnn: Nikoa, ma'az ca asaon so'o macingav?
english: You are welcome. What would you like to know?

bnn: Macingav to ma'az ca kokozaon so'o to talmindoovang aso?
english: What do you do when you are young?

bnn: Sabinaz caak to qabasan, oto molokin caak haipi.
english: I was a police officer but I am retired now.
Then, are you working at the moment?

bnn: Macingav to ihaan acang amin miqomic ca ova'az i soo?
english: Do your kids live in the tribe too?

bnn: Nii, ihaan bokzav ca ova'az naak miqomic.
english: No, my kids are all living in the city.
Then, do you live by yourself?

bnn: Maizang sinaipok naak aco' cin loqai, tatlomaqan naak amin ca naingkon.
english: I also keep a dog and a bird. They are my family.

bnn: Maiza amin ngaong ca saipokon zako, maiza ca sinaipok nanii to maqanciap to makama'az.
english: I have a cat too. I won't get bored with the company of my pet.

bnn: Pacingavang so'on palcicia ito qanop to samo.
english: I would like to ask you about the taboos of hunting.

bnn: Nii to madia ca kitqancaipan naak, oto nataqo'an zako aso ca qancaipon zako.
english: I don't know much about that, but I will tell you everything I know.

bnn: Maiza ito samo ca isqaqanop moo'i?
english: Do you have any taboos about hunting weapons?

bnn: Nii to maqto patido'an binanao'az ca isqaqanop naam.
english: Our hunting weapons are untouchable to women.
Then, can women go hunting together?

bnn: Nii, nii ca binanao'az maqto qanop.
english: No, women cannot go hunting either.

bnn: Bazai, oka'in davoctilac han lomaq qi, nipin aso mabaliv i davoctilac.
english: Kacaw, our home is out of rice wine, please go and buy some.

bnn: Maizang ta'a paan han pitdai'an a. bazin nito mabaliv pana!
english: There is still one bottle left in the kitchen, so there is no need to buy one!

bnn: Patvai ca ta'a paan, nipin maoqnang mabaliv i dosa paan.
english: One bottle is not enough for me, go and buy two more back.

bnn: Mabaliv azak i davoctilac, maiza' imoo?
english: I am looking for rice wine. Do you have any rice wine?

bnn: Haiza na, pia ca nabalivon so'o?
english: Yes! How many bottles do you need?

bnn: Mabaliv azak dosa' paan, maoqnang mabaliv i tatqalop tilac.
english: I want two bottles and a pack of rice.

bnn: Haan dii ca tilac, ma'azing ca doma siza'on soo.
english: Here is the rice, what else do you need?

bnn: Namaoqnang caak mabaliv i qaipoan, maiza' imoo?
english: I want some eggs too, do you have some?

bnn: Aminonin bonon mabaliv ca qaipoan i naam.

english: I want to buy some clothes.
What kind of clothes do you like?

bnn: Mabaliva ki mapocho pakiman to holoc.
english: I want to buy the clothes with short sleeves.
We have white and blue ones too.

bnn: Aiving caak ta'a masanglav to holoc.
english: Please give me the clothes in blue.

bnn: Bazai, maqica aso sangan a? pisqacibang aso sangan?
english: kacaw, where have you been just now? Did you go exercising?

bnn: Nii, mindangaz caak i qodasnao'az naak balivan is sanglav.
english: No, I went grocery shopping for my grandma.

bnn: Maopata dao, maiza inolo'an soo ca sanavanin? maqto ata moskon ma'on qaising.
english: No wonder! Are you available at night? Would you like to have a meal with me?

bnn: Nito maqto, namodan caak mabaliv i holoc.
english: No, I want to buy some clothes.
Then, I will go with you.

bnn: Miqomicng, piia coi ca tatnilaoqot a sanglav dii?
english: Hello, how much is this bunch of vegetables?

bnn: Maposan coi ca tatnilaoqot a sanglav dii.
english: The vegetables are $20 for a bunch.
How much are these sweet potatoes?

bnn: Mati'on coi ca tattingting a hotan dii.
english: Sweet potatoes are thirty dollars for a pound.

bnn: Bato, minpongol caak madas i ispapatas, maqto aso pasimol zakon?
english: ,kacaw I forgot to bring my pen. Can you lend me one?

bnn: Uka' inak amin, icia ca dii ki Kaot.
english: I don't have one either. This is Kaut's.

bnn: Maqto naopa mokhivang pasimol zakon, namahiav caak macaoqais soan.
english: Can you lend me the pen for a second? I will return to you immediately.

bnn: Miqomicang, kadangazing amin miqomicang i Kaot.
english: Thank you and thank Panay for me.

bnn: Macaoqais azak i dosa' to paitasan dii.
english: I want to return these two books.

bnn: Uo, ma'azing ca asaon so'o doma?
english: No problem and what else do you need?

bnn: maoqnang caak simol i taao to paitasan.
english: I would like to borrow these three books.

bnn: Uo na, aka'a to minpongol macaoqais ca taaokinqanin.
english: Sure and remember to return them after three days.

bnn: Ni'ang aso macaoqais zakon isqaqaisqais naak.
english: You haven't returned me the eraser.

bnn: Makoa cona monghav ca isqaqaisqais naak.
english: Then, why is my eraser missing?
Did you lend it to kacaw?

bnn: Nii caak maqanciap, tanamon zako macingav a cia ti.
english: I don't know. I will go and ask her.

bnn: Tangosonang zako aso pasimol i isqaqaisqais naak.
english: I will lend you my eraser first.

bnn: Kaot, icia Bato sinpasimol i soo ca paknata'on i?
english: panay, did kacaw lend you this coat?

bnn: Nii, sinbaliv i tina naak ca kini.
english: No, my mom bought it for me.

bnn: Maszang icia kit Bato ca paknata'on soo.
english: kacaw's coat is the same as yours.

bnn: Niito mazang ca patas naak, madaqdong ca icia.
english: His coat is black, so our colors are different.

bnn: Kaot, misimol aso haan Bato ki coi?
english: panay, did you borrow money from kacaw?

bnn: Uo, ala caoqaison zako haip haan cian a, minpongol caak madas i coi.
english: Yes, I was supposed to return to him today, but I forgot to bring the money.
Then, when will you return the money?
I will return to him tomorrow.

bnn: Uo, nakadangdazan zako aso taqo kit Bato.
english: Okay, I will tell kacaw for you.

bnn: Maca madamo ki qamotic asa makocia ki qato, maca madamo ki tikolac asa makocia ki haqo, maopata namamantok.
english: It is correct to catch mice through rangay and catch bamboo partridges through qjiulang.

bnn: Maopata qana, moliva qana caak, anaqa niito odamoan.
english: No wonder! I am mistaken and that's why I cannot catch any of them.

bnn: Nataqoan zako aso mata'i maidosa' a haqo mangki.
english: Then I will teach you how to set up these two traps.

bnn: Uo, mantan macial, namaqto'in caak odamoan i tosmomot.
english: Great! I will be able to catch the prey in the future.

bnn: Masmotin ca qoma, maipa'a patilacan siza' is kavong, namonqoma ata.
english: The grass in the fields is too tall. Go to the warehouse to take the sickle and let's go to the fields.

bnn: Haan ngalan is palangan, sadoananin ca monkombo aso ki patilacan.
english: It is next to the round basket. You will see it when you enter the warehouse.

bnn: Maloloa ca siza namilolo, manocqaic sala ca kavong.
english: Be careful and don't get hurt. The sickle is very sharp.

bnn: Aka'a to kanpanan ca haqo naak.
Haan nasto is lokic aiza ca haqo naak.
english: My trap is under that tree.

bnn: Maiza sinpacqal naak haan dii, anaqat malolo azak to ica ca haqo naak.
english: I make a mark here, so I know where my trap is.

bnn: Maca dii ka kaan kalala', pihanon zami vaqlac isdamo ki kaan.
english: This is a fish trap which we put beside the river for fishing.

bnn: Uka inam kaan kalala', makocia cam i bosvit maniza is kaan.
english: We don't have any fish traps there, so we catch fish with a fishing rod.

bnn: Ni'ang caak cinokao is bosvit, maqto aso taqo zakon ca moqnin?
english: I have never used a fishing rod before, would you mind teaching me next time?

bnn: Macial na! moskon ata maniza is kaan ca maoqnin.
english: Sure! Let's go fishing together next time.

bnn: Nataqo'an zako aso mata'i ki kaan kalala' ca maqnin.
english: I will teach you how to make a fish trap next time.

bnn: Vindaoqvindaoqin ca bosvit soo i, sado'i ti haizin kaan. mahaiva qan simotmot.
english: Your fishing rod is moving. Isn't the fish on the hook? Pull it up!

bnn: Molo'ang, vivindaoq ca qato, haanti caak sibotbot i bosvit, maipa'a aso maka' kadangaz zakon siza' is ami'.
english: Wait, the ship is rolling heavily. I am here to pull the fishing rod and you should go there to grab me the net.

bnn: Pepai'i dii ca kaan i, kadangazon zako aso sibotbot.
english: Pull the fish to my side and I will help you pull it up.

bnn: Mantan manahip, kabahi ata haip, maqmozin ca kalala'.
